    <main>
        <h1>LeetCode 1784: Check if Binary String Has at Most One Segment of Ones (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Given a binary string s without leading zeros, return true if s contains at most one contiguous segment
                of ones. Otherwise, return false. A segment of ones is a contiguous sequence of one or more '1's.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: s = "1001"<br>
                Output: false<br>
                Explanation: The string has two segments of ones: "1" at the beginning and "1" at the end.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    bool checkOnesSegment(string s) {
        for (int i = 1; i &lt; s.size(); i++) {
            // "01" directly creates another ones segment
            if (s[i - 1] == '0' &amp;&amp; s[i] == '1') return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
};</code></pre>
